Rewrite the candidate's resume to align with the target JD using a
**recency-weighted strategy**.

# TIER STRATEGY (ABSOLUTE)

Each role below carries a [TIER] tag — apply this exact strategy per tier:

- **RECENT** (the candidate's current/most recent role): Inject EVERY JD
  must-have technology and domain keyword into this role's bullets, intro,
  and skills line wherever it can fit a real achievement framing. Mirror
  the JD's exact phrases. You MAY add 1–2 NEW bullets (max) to this role
  to surface JD must-haves that don't fit existing bullets — append them
  at the end of the bullets list. This is where the recruiter looks for fit.
- **MID** (mid-tenure roles): Apply JD signals only when they fit
  naturally. If the role's existing skills_line lists Redis and the JD
  wants Kafka (same domain), swap. If the JD wants a wholly new tech that
  has no analogue in this role, leave it alone.
- **OLDEST** (the candidate's earliest listed role): COPY EVERY FIELD
  BYTE-FOR-BYTE FROM THE INPUT. Do not rephrase, do not substitute, do
  not "improve" anything. This role showcases career breadth.

# JD ANALYSIS

must_have:
{% for item in jd.must_have %}
  - {{ item.tech }} ({{ item.category }}) — "{{ item.evidence }}"
{% else %}
  (none)
{% endfor %}

nice_to_have:
{% for item in jd.nice_to_have %}
  - {{ item.tech }} ({{ item.category }})
{% else %}
  (none)
{% endfor %}

soft_skills: {{ jd.soft_skills | join(", ") or "(none)" }}
domain_keywords: {{ jd.domain_keywords | join(", ") or "(none)" }}
exact_phrases_to_mirror:
{% for phrase in jd.exact_phrases_to_mirror %}
  - "{{ phrase }}"
{% else %}
  (none)
{% endfor %}
seniority_level: {{ jd.seniority_level }}

# CANDIDATE RESUME (current)

header_title: {{ resume.header.title or "(none)" }}

summary:
"""
{{ resume.summary.text }}
"""

experience:
{% for role in resume.experience %}
ROLE {{ loop.index0 }} of {{ resume.experience | length }}  [TIER: {{ tiers[loop.index0] | upper }}]
  company:  {{ role.company }}
  title:    {{ role.title }}
  dates:    {{ role.dates }}
  location: {{ role.location }}
  intro:    "{{ role.intro }}"
  bullets:
  {% for b in role.bullets %}
    [{{ loop.index0 }}] "{{ b }}"
  {% endfor %}
  skills_line: "{{ role.skills_line or "" }}"
{% endfor %}

skills_section (existing categories):
{% for cat, items in resume.skills_section.categories.items() %}
  {{ cat }}: {{ items | join(", ") }}
{% endfor %}

{% if prior_issues %}
# PRIOR ATTEMPT VALIDATION FAILED

The previous attempt produced these critical issues. Fix them this time:
{% for issue in prior_issues %}
  - {{ issue.section }}: {{ issue.issue }}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

# HARD RULES (the Validator WILL reject violations)

1. PRESERVE every company name, employment date, degree, field of study,
   location, and the candidate's seniority word ("Senior", "Staff",
   "Principal") byte-for-byte from the input.
2. PRESERVE every number, percentage, year, currency amount, and quantified
   metric exactly as written. Units stay too ("ms", "rps", "M", "k", "x").
3. OLDEST tier role: output its intro, every bullet, and its skills_line
   byte-for-byte from the input. No exceptions.
4. NEW BULLETS only in the RECENT role, up to 2. They must describe
   plausible achievements consistent with the candidate's overall trajectory.
5. NEVER use any banned word: {{ banned_words | join(", ") }}.
6. header_title may add a comma-separated JD-aligned suffix (e.g.
   "SENIOR SOFTWARE ENGINEER, BACKEND PLATFORMS") but must contain the
   original title text as a prefix substring.
7. Every existing bullet rewrite must stay within ±25% of its original
   character count.

# OUTPUT — JSON ONLY

Return exactly this shape (no markdown fences, no prose, no commentary):

{
  "header_title": "<full new title — original text must be a prefix>",
  "summary_text": "<rewritten summary>",
  "experience": [
    {
      "intro": "<rewritten or verbatim per tier>",
      "bullets": ["<rewritten bullets in original order>", "<...possibly new bullets if RECENT>"],
      "skills_line": "<rewritten or verbatim per tier; null if the role had no skills line>"
    }
    // ... one entry per input role, in the SAME order
  ],
  "skills_section_categories": {
    "<Category Name>": ["<item>", "<item>"]
    // include every category from the input; you may add items reflecting JD must-haves
  }
}
